            <p>The origins of <b>street art</b> dates back to the 60s of the last century. Originally known only in the United States, effectively distributed, it has become well-known in the 80s in Europe. Street art is a form of visual art created in public spaces, initially known mainly as graffiti. It is worth mentioning that street art is also all kinds of murals, vlepki, posters and installations.</p>
            <p>This art has the task of specific incarnation in the surrounding area, on the other hand, should attract attention and entail appropriate message of the artist, which it usually is anonymous and only its creativity is able to speak to his audience. The recipients of that art are all people who are in a given space, regardless of whether they are aware of it or not. Often, street art is sadly mistaken associated with vandalism, because art is often created illegally and artists working in secret.</p>
            <p>Examples of world-renowned artists are street art Banksy, Richard "Richie" Miranda, Jeff Brown, Shepard Fairey, Donald Joseph White. Particularly noteworthy is the so-called 3D Street Painting. 3D Street Painting is a three-dimensional trompe l'oeil painting. Although that is created on the street or the floor, it gives the impression of an extraordinary reality, rise above the plane or the illusion of an endless abyss, all this making good use of the principles of perspective. Only perfectly defined deformation of the image, will create the illusion of real objects and space. With a remarkable performance, 3D Street Painting becomes the world's growing in popularity. In Poland, the art is still relatively little known, although a group of supporters is gradually increasing. Not surprisingly, as it is surprising, inspiring awe and curiosity. Undoubted plus paintings in this technique is the possibility of interaction that occurs between the image and the man who becomes an integral part of it. Then, it depends on the creativity of how the change of the connecting composition.</p>
