            <p>The message of street art can have political overtones, social as well as educational. Very many artists expressed through street art his vision of art and beauty and the ability to satisfy the aesthetic and visual deficiency of a large group of customers who are very appreciate the positive impact of street art in all kinds, often depressing, public spaces.</p>
            <p>Street art in a sense has become, at least in some parts of the world, an indispensable element of the urban environment. It is not only in the streets but also in parks, subway and other spaces not only the urban public. Some people think of street art is a way of life, sometimes even a way of life. It attributed also to the term colloquially speaking loose and stress, distanced approach to the everyday world, both to the subjects as weighty and specific fun ways of spending free time. Various subcultures derive from street art and its ubiquity somehow been absorbed naturally by the fashion world. Increasingly, we hear that it is street art has become an Services and a genuine Services to create fashion. Not only by niche designers but also the world-famous. In a sense, street art became simply fashionable, what is more, has a chance to be fashionable forever, because naturally changes over time.</p>
